{
  "description": "BigQuery-MariaDB hybrid featuring PIVOT/UNPIVOT as first-class FROM-clause operators, aggregate FILTER spelled as WHERE inside aggregate parens, reversed EXCEPT/INTERSECT precedence via explicit CORRESPONDING BY, and semicolon-separated comma joins.",
  "divergence_level": "moderate",
  "inspired_by": [
    "bigquery",
    "mariadb"
  ],
  "name": "bigmaria_pivot",
  "notes": "Hybrid of BigQuery (case-preserving identifiers, 0-based arrays, PIVOT/UNPIVOT in FROM clause, c_style boolean truthiness) and MariaDB (backtick quoting, hash comments, LIKE case-insensitive, div-by-zero yields NULL, requires semicolon). Headline axes: (1) SET ops require CORRESPONDING BY column list (INTERSECT CORRESPONDING BY / EXCEPT CORRESPONDING BY), (2) aggregate FILTER spelled as WHERE inside aggregate parens (convention, not keyword), (3) PIVOT/UNPIVOT as first-class FROM-clause operators, (4) 0-based array indexing. Conflicts with prior slots: differs from snowacle_qualify on row limiting (LIMIT vs QUALIFY), CTE keyword (WITH vs DEFINE), null ordering defaults (last/last vs first/first), identifier quoting (backtick vs double); differs from redgres_lateral on concat (|| operator vs CONCAT_WS-only), join style (standard vs LATERAL-mandatory), array base (0 vs default); differs from mydb2_rollup on row limiting (LIMIT vs ROWNUM), modulo (% vs MOD), null-safe-eq (IS NOT DISTINCT FROM vs EQUALS_NULL), identifier quoting (backtick vs double).",
